Geshdo is a JS based web tool employing scrum and kanban methodologies in combination with scheduling components to structure and manage a to-do list and your time.

Requires:
node
express
elasticsearch
child_process

Uses ElasticSearch as a backend storage and Kibana for exploring the data

Note:
WiP

Install:
mkdir Geshdo
cd Geshdo

#Install ElasticSearch
wget https://download.elasticsearch.org/elasticsearch/release/org/elasticsearch/distribution/zip/elasticsearch/2.0.0/elasticsearch-2.0.0.zip

unzip elasticsearch-2.0.0.zip

rm elasticsearch-2.0.0.zip

sudo aptitude install openjdk-7-jre openjdk-7-jre-headless openjdk-7-jre-lib openjdk-7-jdk
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/bin/java

./elasticsearch-2.0.0/bin/elasticsearch.in.sh

#Install Kibana
wget https://download.elastic.co/kibana/kibana/kibana-4.2.0-linux-x64.tar.gz

tar -xzvf kibana-4.2.0-linux-x64.tar.gz

rm kibana-4.2.0-linux-x64.tar.gz

#Install Geshdo
git clone ssh://git.amazon.com/pkg/Geshdo
cd Geshdo

npm install express elasticsearch

../elasticsearch-2.0.0/bin/elasticsearch &

../kibana-4.2.0-linux-x64/bin/kibana &

node geshdo.js &

Browse:
http://localhost:3000/#
